gan to play the audience back to wakefulness from the dreamlike state that the flutes melody had provided them into. <br><br><br>"This next story is a tale told to me by a dear Teir'dal Enchantress," Casidy spoke clearly. <br><br><br>(to view the tale she told go here: <a href="http://www.viper.tierranet.com/Drunkards/Features/Inia/08032000.html"> Political discussion about pie as a projectile range weapon </a>)<br><br><br>Her story elicited the expected result, cheers and laughter filled the room. Picking up her third glass of mead, she downed the glass, and began to pack up the tips tossed her way. <br><br><br>One more round she thought should finish me for the night. Moving past Qwik, she leaned over to whisper, "I need some air, after I pass another round, I will be outside for a stroll, would you care to protect a wee drunken bard from the wilds of the Commonlands?" <br><br><br>Hardly pausing for his reply, she headed back to the bar, filled a tray with drinks, and moved around the tables again. <br><br> <p><br><b><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2 COLOR="#6699cc">---------------------------<br> Silent, Deadly         <br> Yeah, Right                  <br>---------------------------<br><br>~ Casidy Noteworthy</font></b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ujzonn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jzonn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/8/01 9:43:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://personal.bhm.bellsouth.net/bhm/r/p/rpo2/Jzonn_Icon.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Yet another beginning...</span><hr size=1> The door to the inn opens slowly.  The slight whine from the hinges attest to the need for oil on them.  At first, the barest of outlines could be seen from the night sky.  Slowly, a figure emerges from the darkness.  His armor is of a green hue, but appears to be made of differing types.  At his right side is coiled a whip.  A set of fangs or perhaps talons hang from his left.  The pack he carries appears worn and weighted.<br><br>As he makes his way in, he carefully closes the door.  Turning back around to move further into the room, he inadvertantly bumps into a Teir'dal who appears to be on her way out.  &quot;My apologies, lass.  I don't seem to have my normal legs right now&quot;, he offers with a tilt of his head.  She returns a scowl, but backs away a bit upon seeing the gaunt look in his eyes.  He hardly notices as he moves over to the bar.<br><br>The barkeep casts a wary eye at the newcomer, but listens as he hears the request.  &quot;I'd like to get some hot brandy, please.  I'll be sitting over at that far table when it's ready.  I'll tip yer servant well if they'll bring it to me.&quot;  With that, he tosses a few coins on the counter and moves over to the empty table.  He takes his pack off and sets it next to a chair he eases into.<br><br>The barkeep walks over to the fire and pulls a poker off the wall.  He sticks it in the coals and returns to his bar.  After filling a few other drink orders, he decants some brandy into a metal container of unknown composition.  He moves back over to the fire and takes the poker out of the coals, taps it against the inside of the fireplace to remove as much of the soot as possible, and sticks it inside the cup.  The sound of bubbling liquid can be heard and a steam rises from the cup, wafting about the room.  After the brandy is heated, the barkeep returns to the bar and pours it into a glass straining it through a cloth to remove any remaining debris.  The glass is placed on the counter while the barkeep motions for a pick up. <p><B><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#3A6EA5">Jzonn Stormwolf &lt;Final Destiny&gt;</B></FONT><BR><I><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#cfcfcf">Ranger of Karana</I></FONT></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/bayonaero.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=qwik>Qwik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New to the block</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/9/01 3:33:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Yet another beginning...</span><hr size=1> pausing to let the new patron to pass bye Qwik nodded his head at him and grabbed the slowly closing door and headed just outside the building ... a slight shiver passed through his body as a slight breeze briskly danced over his skin. leaning aginst the building falling deep into though taking a moment to reflect on the past months of training and then sighing in deep relif , thankfull that he will have some time to rest and relax after all he was recently through. after months in solitude with nothing but his thoughts and training it was always a welcome pleasure to see a warm face, especially one like Casidy whos beauty couldn't even be given any justice by the songs of the greatest songreaver in the land. <br>Stairing up at the sky qwik sat back on the ground outside of the door awaiting the his friend eagerly. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ucasidy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Casidy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/9/01 6:01:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Yet another beginning...</span><hr size=1> Casidy made her rounds to the patrons, and headed up to the bar, to deliver the special drink order the new arrival had ordered.<br><br>The barkeep whispered something to Casidy, about the patron being weary, but having a heavy coin. Casidy giggled at him, the silly man, always after every last copper he could out of his customers.<br><br>Casidy let him know this would be her last delivery, and that she was going out, for a bit.<br><br>Walking the warm brandy over to the patron, she tripped over the leg of one of the younger paladins sitting that had moved his leg to stretch it, spilling the extremely hot contents down the front of her blouse.<br><br>"Youch!" Casidy shrieked. As she tumbled the remainder of the way falling into the arms of the aging paladin who happened to have risen just in time to catch her as she fell.<br><br>Helping her up, she apologized and blushed, as all eyes in the bar turned to her.<br><br>"Well, it seems my clumsy feet have gotten the better of me again" Casidy sighed. <br><br>Moving back to the bar, the other server came up to help clean up the mess, and allow Casidy to go prepare the brandy again.<br><br>Sighing to herself as she walked the second glass of hot liquid over to the weary patron. "Here you are dear, sorry for the delay, I seemed to have needed a bit of brandy to warm myself as well."<br> <p><br><b><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2 COLOR="#6699cc">---------------------------<br> Silent, Deadly         <br> Yeah, Right                  <br>---------------------------<br><br>~ Casidy Noteworthy</font></b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ujzonn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jzonn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/9/01 6:37:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://personal.bhm.bellsouth.net/bhm/r/p/rpo2/Jzonn_Icon.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Yet another beginning...</span><hr size=1> As the young lady approaches, a Bard by appearances to the man in green, she places the glass on the table.  The glass has a cloth wrapped around it to help in the handling of the hot contents.  The man smells the brandy fumes coming from the glass.  He looks up and gives a slight smile as he reaches into a side pouch.  He places several gold coins on the table.  &quot;Thank you, lass.  This will do quite nicely.  Hot brandy has such a calming effect.&quot;<br><br>The Bard scoops up the coins in a fluid motion with her left hand to indicate that, while her feet may appear clumsy at the moment, her fingers are nimble.  As she turns to walk back to the bar, the man quickly, but gently, catches her right hand.  &quot;Don't worry about the incident with the other glass.  'Tis good to see yer not injured.&quot;  While speaking, he carefully palms a few more brighter coins into her right hand and winks.<br><br>As she walks off with a puzzled look, the man turns to his glass and cups it with both hands.  Bringing it to his face, resting on his lower lip, but not turned up for drinking.  He breaths in deeply and savors the aroma for a moment.  The glass is tilted to allow a small amount to pour out.  The man grimaces for a second, but relaxes as the amber liquid flows over his tongue and finally down his throat.  The glass is returned to the table as he leans back in his chair, noticably relaxing while his eyes begin to stare at the flames in the fireplace across the room. <p><B><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#3A6EA5">Jzonn Stormwolf &lt;Final Destiny&gt;</B></FONT><BR><I><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#cfcfcf">Ranger of Karana</I></FONT></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http:/